DTEND:20260505T064200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.379ft at 06:12\n-0.043ft at 06:42\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Slow fading combo of NW/WNW and SSW swell shows best in the morning with w
 aist-chest-shoulder high surf\, as standouts hit head high. Waves graduall
 y dip during the day along with the easing swell. Early morning drained by
  a negative low tide\, then incoming tide push lends a hand through mid da
 y.\n\nLight/variable winds due in the morning\, followed by a light+ SW af
 ternoon sea breeze. 
END:VEVENT
